The last time was at the end of this month. The city administration attributes this to the rumors that swirled around the former director of the zoo and veterinarian Václav Poživil that he purposefully killed the exotic animals he cared for. For example, it was a female rhino Zamba, an elephant Kalu or an orangutan Ňuňák.
The city council has therefore announced a new contract. "For veterinary care for the zoo with an estimated value of 3.5 million crowns excluding VAT and for the city's Centre for Animals in Need with an estimated value of 2.8 million crowns excluding VAT," said city spokeswoman Romana Macová.
