"It is necessary to remember what happened here, the horror," said Babiš. The attack on the USA on 11 September 2001 was described by the Prime Minister as a reason why the United Nations should cooperate in a united campaign against international terrorism. In addition to the destruction of the WTC skyscrapers, the terrorists crashed a hijacked plane into the building of the Ministry of Defence in Washington and were planning another strike on a target in Washington, probably the White House or Congress. However, this plane crashed when the passengers stood up to the hijackers.
"This is our main enemy, where all the countries of the world should unite and fight against international terrorism in a coordinated manner," the Czech Prime Minister added.
