Wife swap: Ondra was cruelly abused by his parents and ended up in an institution
It was nerve-wracking. The allegedly troubled son Ondřej (9) was severely punished by his father at every moment. "He came home from school and lied about having a snack. Lukáš looked at me and said that he would kneel as punishment," Lucie described in Exchange. Dad Lukáš forced little Ondřej to kneel in a corner for several hours! In addition, away from the cameras, he had to suffer like this on a wooden mat to massage his feet! "Ondřej came to me after the shooting and told me - aunt, I am making these troubles and notes just so that I am not here, because I want to go to an institution," Lucie described the moment when she fully understood what was happening behind the door of the studio. And the boy's wish finally came true...
His condition was so serious that he was taken away from his family after the shooting and placed in the Centre for Educational Care in České Budějovice for a month. He returned to his father and surrogate mother Aneta (28) for a short time, but then went to a diagnostic institute for troubled children. "When I arrived home, Aneta immediately added me on Facebook, we wrote to each other for a while. She was most interested in whether we had received money. I almost did not respond to that. But then she wrote to me that the little one was in the institute, that he was then returned to them, now he is in the diagnostic centre. They are both out of work," says mother Lucie from Pilsen.
Of course, Blesk also reached out to the other party, but received only a vague response. "I'm not in the mood, I'm sick, call back later," Aneta said and hung up the phone.
Přindiš, Prskavec and Fišerová safely advanced to the semi-finals of the World Championship
Kayakers Vít Přindiš and Jiří Prskavec and canoeist Tereza Fišerová safely advanced to the semi-finals of the ICF Canoe Slalom World Championships in Seu d'Urgell. Přindiš was fourth in Friday's qualification, Prskavec fifth and Fišerová eighth. Three other Czech representatives will be aiming for a semi-final start in Spain in the afternoon corrective qualifying race.
From the strong representative group of kayakers, Vavřinec Hradilek did not succeed, who received a fifty-second penalty right at the beginning of the ride for incorrectly passing the gate. Přindiš and Prskavec, on the other hand, can now rest and concentrate on Sunday's semi-final.
"I set myself the goal of making it into the top 30 in the first run, which I managed to do. Not that I didn't care how I did, because on Sunday the start is very early in the morning, so I was hoping to be a little higher to have a better starting position," said Přindiš, praising his well-being in Seo. "Before the patrol race I felt the worst in the 14 days we've been here. Then during the race it was good and today it was better again. It's been beautiful here all the time, nice races, the spectators came, so it's fine," he smiled.
Prskavec was also satisfied. "In qualifying, you don't want to make an unnecessary mistake. In the first gates, I didn't quite get it. Then I drove the middle perfectly, without any problems and I knew I had the mileage, so the second mistake came when I wanted to go straight down and I turned the erka. Overall, I can't be dissatisfied. The form is there, we'll see how it goes," said this year's overall World Cup winner.
Both representatives praised the fact that they will go to the start on Sunday only at the end of the semi-final block. "I'm not an early bird, it's also cold here in the morning, and when you're here at eight, you want to have a jacket and a sweatshirt," said Přindiš. "Overall, the semi-final takes an hour and a half, which is quite a good difference in terms of sleep," agreed Prskavec.
Of the three Czech canoeists, only Fišerová succeeded, Eva Říhová finished two places behind the top twenty, Kateřina Havlíčková was 35th. "I skied the upper part according to my expectations, in the middle passage it seemed to me that I couldn't keep up and I wasn't going according to plan, but I managed to get into the comfortable track that I wanted to go. I made two shots and I'm just behind the winner with a clean time. I have a good starting position for the semifinals," Fišerová praised.
