4.2 The Client shall pay the Remuneration on the basis of tax documents issued by the Contractor. The tax document shall be issued by the Contractor after the expiry of the month for which the tax document is issued. If the Client requests the Contractor to do so, the Contractor shall attach to the tax document a monthly statement of the Services provided for the given period. The Contractor shall indicate the amount of the Remuneration excluding value added tax (VAT) on the tax document. The day of taxable performance shall be the last day of the period for which the Contractor invoices the Services.
4.3 The Client shall pay the remuneration to the Contractor to the bank account indicated on the relevant tax document. On all its tax documents, the Contractor shall indicate only the bank account that its tax administrator has published in a manner allowing remote access (i.e. the bank account indicated in the Register of VAT payers).
4.4 The remuneration is due 30 days from the date on which the tax document was delivered to the Client.
4.5 If the tax document
4.5.1 does not contain the legal requirements; or if
4.5.2 contains incorrect price information; or if
