10. Acceptance Procedure, Delivery Handover Upgrade to Acceptance Procedure
10.1 The aim of the Acceptance Procedure is to verify whether the result of the Contractor's activities is consistent with the Specification and the Change Documentation of the Changes included in the Upgrade Delivery. Furthermore, the aim of the Acceptance Procedure is to verify whether the Incidents included in the Upgrade Delivery have been resolved.
10.2 The requirements and steps of the Acceptance Procedure are listed in Appendix No. 9 (Acceptance Procedure). Part of the Acceptance Procedure are the acceptance criteria that the Upgrade Delivery must meet.
10.3 If the Contractor demonstrates the result of its activities under this Agreement to the Client and proves the results of unit and integration tests carried out on such a result, the Contractor shall hand over the result of its activities to the Client for the Acceptance Procedure.
10.4 The Parties shall write a report on the submission of the result of the activity to the Contractor for the Acceptance Procedure. The Contractor shall submit a draft of the Report on the Submission of the Upgrade Delivery for the Acceptance Procedure. The draft of the Report on the Submission of the Upgrade Delivery for the Acceptance Procedure always contains the result of unit and integration tests. A sample of the Report on the Submission of the Upgrade Delivery for the Acceptance Procedure is contained in Annex No. 10 (Sample of the Report on the Submission of the Upgrade Delivery for the Acceptance Procedure).
11. Initiation, course and termination of the Acceptance Procedure of the Upgrade Delivery
11.1 Without undue delay, after the Parties have signed the Record of Delivery of the Upgrade to the Acceptance Procedure, they will agree on the time schedule for the implementation of the Acceptance Procedure and the Customer will start the Acceptance Procedure.
11.2 During the implementation of the Acceptance Procedure, the Client shall list the Incidents that have affected the result of the Contractor's activities in comparison with the required characteristics of the Upgrade Delivery and shall submit this list to the Contractor. The Client may also report the Incidents to the Contractor during the implementation of the Acceptance Procedure. During the Acceptance Procedure, the Contractor may resolve the Incidents, remove the defects and, in accordance with the agreed procedures, submit the corrected result of its activities to the Client for further implementation of the Acceptance Procedure.
11.3 The acceptance procedure is terminated either:
11.3.1 by completing all steps of the Acceptance Procedure, resolving all reported Incidents and correcting all identified defects in the Upgrade Delivery; or
11.3.2 by the end of the period determined by the agreed time schedule for the implementation of the Acceptance Procedure; or
11.3.3 if, during the implementation of the Acceptance Procedure, the number of Incidents, which are defects, exceeds the number of defects specified in the acceptance criteria, which gives the Customer the right to stop the Acceptance Procedure.
12. Successful completion of the Upgrade Delivery Acceptance Procedure
12.1 If all the steps of the Acceptance Procedure have been carried out, and if the Upgrade Delivery meets all the acceptance criteria specified in Appendix No. 9 (Acceptance Procedure), and if by the end of the Acceptance Procedure the Contractor has resolved all reported Incidents of the result of its activities and removed all identified defects of the result of its activities, the Acceptance Procedure will be terminated as successful without reservations.
12.2 If all the steps of the Acceptance Procedure have been carried out and if the Upgrade Delivery meets all the acceptance criteria specified in Appendix No. 9 (Acceptance Procedure), and if by the end of the Acceptance Procedure the Contractor has not resolved all the reported Incidents of the result of its activities and has not eliminated all the identified defects of the result of its activities, the Acceptance Procedure shall be terminated as successful with reservation.
12.3 If the Acceptance Procedure is concluded as successful, the Parties shall draw up a Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for Use. The Contractor shall submit a draft of the Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for Use. If the Upgrade Delivery has defects, the draft of such a record always contains a list of defects and the required deadline for their removal. The Parties shall sign the record no later than one (1) week from the date on which the Customer expressed its consent to the draft of the Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for Use. The model of such a record of acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for Use is Annex No. 11 (Model of the Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for Use).
12.4 If the Acceptance Procedure is concluded as successful subject to the removal of defects, the Contractor shall remove all defects within the deadlines specified in the Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for Use. The Contractor shall hand over the repaired Delivery to the Customer for repeated verification. If the Contractor does not remove all defects within the deadlines specified in the Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for Use, the Contractor is in default.
12.5 By signing the Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for Use, (1) the Customer confirms that at the time of signing such a record, the Upgrade Delivery does not have defects that prevent the use of the Application and (2) the Contractor declares that the Upgrade Delivery is made in accordance with the Specification and the Change Documentation of the Changes included in the Upgrade and Czech law. The moment in which the last Party signs the Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for Use is the moment in which (1) the Contractor has fulfilled its obligation to make the Delivery and (2) the Customer acquires ownership of the Delivery.
12.6 Even if the Customer is in delay with the takeover of the Upgrade Delivery, the Contractor does not have the right to sell the Upgrade Delivery to a third party. If the Customer takes over the Upgrade Delivery, the rights from the obvious defect of the Upgrade Delivery are retained, even if the Contractor objects to the court that the right was not exercised in time.
13. Unsuccessful completion of the Acceptance Procedure of the Upgrade Delivery
13.1 If the Upgrade Delivery does not meet the acceptance criteria specified in Appendix No. 9 (Acceptance Procedure), the Acceptance Procedure shall be terminated as unsuccessful. The Acceptance Procedure shall also be terminated as unsuccessful if, during the implementation of the Acceptance Procedure, the number of defects found by the Customer exceeds the number of defects specified in the acceptance criteria, which gives the Customer the right to stop the Acceptance Procedure. If the Acceptance Procedure is terminated as unsuccessful, the Customer shall write down the defects that have occurred in the Acceptance Procedure submitted to the Upgrade Delivery and return this list, together with the Upgrade Delivery, to the Contractor.
13.2 If the Acceptance Procedure is terminated as unsuccessful, the Contractor shall be deemed not to have delivered the Upgrade Delivery to perform the Acceptance Procedure. The relevant Record of Delivery of the Upgrade Delivery to perform the Acceptance Procedure shall be regarded as if it had never been created.
13.3 If the Contractor does not hand over the Upgrade Delivery in time for the Acceptance Procedure, the Contractor is in default.
13.4 If the Acceptance Procedure is terminated as unsuccessful, the Contractor shall remove the defects that led to the termination of the Acceptance Procedure as unsuccessful as soon as possible and hand over the repaired Delivery to the Customer for the repeated Acceptance Procedure. The costs of the repeated Acceptance Procedure shall be borne by the Contractor.
14. Acceptance Procedure for Patch Delivery
14.1 The aim of the Acceptance Procedure is to verify whether the result of the Contractor's activities has resolved the Incident or Incidents included in the Patch Delivery.
14.2 The requirements and steps of the Acceptance Procedure are listed in Appendix No. 9 (Acceptance Procedure). Part of the Acceptance Procedure are the acceptance criteria that the Patch Delivery must meet.
14.3 Without undue delay after the Contractor submits the Patch Delivery for the Acceptance Procedure, the Customer shall start the Acceptance Procedure.
14.4 In the course of carrying out the Acceptance Procedure, the Customer shall verify whether the Incidents contained in the Patch Delivery have been resolved.
14.5 If all steps of the Acceptance Procedure have been performed, and if the Patch Delivery meets all the acceptance criteria specified in Appendix No. 9 (Acceptance Criteria), the Acceptance Procedure shall be terminated as successful. If the Patch Delivery has not resolved all the Incidents included therein, the Supplier shall resolve such Incidents in the next Patch Delivery. Such Incidents shall be regarded as unresolved and the Customer shall be entitled to a contractual penalty.
14.6 If the Patch Delivery does not meet the acceptance criteria specified in Annex No. 9 (Acceptance Procedure), the Acceptance Procedure shall be terminated as unsuccessful and the Customer shall write down the defects that have manifested themselves in the Patch Delivery submitted for the Acceptance Procedure and return this list, together with the Patch Delivery, to the Contractor.
15. Source code
15.1 If a source code is created during the provision of the Services, the Contractor shall hand over this source code to the Client upon acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery, in a sealed package. The Client has the right to check the source code against, for example, malicious code or security risks, or for the purpose of complying with the regulations of the supervisory authority.
15.2 If, even after a second written request, which the Client sends to the Contractor no earlier than three (3) weeks after the date of sending the first request, the Contractor does not provide assistance in solving a problem related to the Application, the Client has the right to use the source code in any way, including modifying it or handing it over to a third party for the purpose of modification.
15.3 The Source Code shall be handed over by the Contractor to the Customer in editable electronic form, in the format of the given development environment and in the version that corresponds to the current version of the Application. The Source Code shall be handed over by the Contractor to the Customer no later than on the day on which the Parties sign the Record of Acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for Use. Together with the Source Code, the Contractor shall hand over to the Customer all materials related to the Source Code.
