Annex No. 9 / Acceptance procedure
The items listed below are only inspirational. This appendix must be formulated precisely and exhaustively by the project manager.
Delivery of the Upgrade
Acceptance criteria for the Upgrade Delivery to start the Acceptance procedure
Delivery of an incremental version of those parts of the Application in the form of executable codes affected by the Upgrade
Delivery of the current version of the Functional Specification and Documentation of those parts of the Application that are affected by the Upgrade
Successful implementation of the installation Upgrade to the UAT environment according to the installation procedure, whereby the installation is carried out by an employee of the Customer with the assistance of employees of the Contractor
Successful demonstration of the Changes and Incidents included in the Upgrade, whereby the demonstration will be carried out by the Contractor's employees and will be marked as successful if 80% of the demonstrated functionality runs without problems
Acceptance criteria for the Upgrade Delivery for the implementation of the Acceptance Procedure
Successful completion of the UAT (by implementing all relevant test scenarios), with the UAT being completed as successful if the delivered Upgrade contains no more than the following number of unclosed Incidents:
Category TA incident: 0 (none)
Category TB incident: 3 (three)
Category TC incident: 10 (ten)
Successful execution of business critical scenarios in a UAT environment, where no business critical scenario will have a TA, TB or TC incident
The Upgrade Delivery acceptance procedure may be terminated even if the number of at one time unresolved Incidents from the UAT environment, which are defects in the Application or Documentation, reaches or exceeds the following number of unresolved Incidents:
Category TA incident: 5 (five)
Category TB incident: 10 (ten)
Category TC incident: 30 (thirty)
Patch delivery
Acceptance Criteria for Patch Delivery
Delivery of an incremental version of those parts of the Application in the form of executable codes affected by the Patch
Delivery of the current version of the Functional Specification and Documentation of those parts of the Application that are affected by the Patch, and if it is expedient to resolve the Incident / incidents, these parts can also be delivered in the next Upgrade
Successful verification of the resolution of the Incident/Incidents included in the Patch, while the Patch must not show any Incidents
If the Patch has not resolved all the Incidents included in it, it is up to the Customer to decide whether to mark the Acceptance Procedure as successful
