Annex 12 / Safety rules
1. Definition of terms
1.1 For the purposes of this Annex, the following terms and phrases shall have the meanings set out below:
Security incident means any breach of the confidentiality, integrity or availability of Information Assets.
Information asset means any information, process, hardware or software component that (1) supports the business activities of the Authorized Entity, or (2) has value to the Authorized Entity, or (3) whose disclosure, unauthorized modification or unavailability has a negative impact on the Authorized Entity.
Persons of the Contractor means persons who are directly or indirectly involved in the performance of the subject matter of this Agreement, including persons of the Contractor's subcontractors.
The environment of the Authorized Entity means the premises in which the Authorized Entity carries out its business activities and the information and communication systems that the Authorized Entity uses and that contain Information Assets.
2. Personnel security
2.1 None of the Contractor's Persons:
2.1.1 has no criminal record;
2.1.2 has not been convicted of an intentional criminal offence in the past and is not being prosecuted at the time of performance of the subject matter of this Agreement,
2.2 If the Contractor finds that the Contractor's Persons do not comply with the above rules, they must immediately inform the Client of this. The Client is entitled to demand that such a person no longer participate in the implementation of work arising from the subject matter of this Agreement, either directly or indirectly, and is entitled to demand that the Contractor ensure adequate compensation.
2.3 The Contractor shall provide the Client with a complete list of the names of the Contractor's Persons. The Contractor undertakes to inform the Client in advance of any changes in the staffing arrangements for the performance of this Agreement.
2.4 Persons of the Contractor:
2.4.1 they must be familiar with these safety rules,
2.4.2 have all the necessary examinations and attestations that arise from the law or the requirements of the regulator for the type of work they are to perform in connection with the performance of this Agreement,
2.4.3 are regularly trained by the Supplier in the areas of information security.
2.5 The Contractor's Persons may not enter the Environment of the Authorized Entity under the influence of addictive, narcotic or psychotropic substances or bring weapons, explosives, flammable substances, means of combat, poisons, radioactive and toxic substances, or any other substances that endanger human life and/or health.
3. Physical security
3.1 The access of the Contractor's Persons to the Environment of the Authorized Entity is permitted only if their presence is necessary for the performance of the work obligations arising from this Agreement.
3.2 The persons of the Contractor are always accompanied by a responsible employee of the Client in the Environment of the Authorized Entity.
3.3 The free movement of the Contractor's Persons in the Environment of the Authorized Entity is permitted only if the person has been issued a personal access card. The Contractor's Person may not further lend the access card to third parties or allow third parties to access the Environment of the Authorized Entity.
3.4 In case of loss of the access card or in case of suspicion of loss of the access card, the Contractor is obliged to inform the Client without delay.
3.5 Without undue delay after the completion of the work arising from this Agreement or after the termination of this Agreement, or if further physical access of the Contractor's Persons to the Authorised Entity's Environment is no longer necessary, the Client shall ensure that all Contractor's Persons return the borrowed access cards to the Client.
3.6 Without the prior written consent of the Client, the Contractor may not remove any Information Assets from the Authorized Entity's Environment by means of a storage medium.
4. Identification and authentication of the Contractor's Persons in the Authorized Entity Environment
4.1 The Contractor's persons are assigned only accounts that allow unambiguous identification of the user and only with such authorizations as are necessary for the performance of their work obligations under this Agreement.
4.2 The Contractor performs routine work tasks under non-privileged accounts, accounts with administrator privileges are used only in necessary cases.
4.3 The Contractor's persons may not access the Internet if they are working under an account with administrator privileges or with applications that are running under administrator privileges.
4.4 Inactive accounts of the Contractor's Persons are proactively reported by the Contractor to the Client.
4.5 Shared accounts are used by the Contractor only with the prior written consent of the Client.
4.6 In the event of disclosure of the password or in the event of suspicion that the password has been disclosed, the Contractor must immediately ensure that the password is changed or blocked.
5. Dealing with certificates
5.1 Access to certificates (both logical and physical) will be granted only to those Contractor's Persons for whom such access is necessary for the performance of their work duties.
5.2 The Contractor may not provide the certificates or make them available to third parties without the written consent of the Client.
5.3 After their installation, the certificates can only be stored in a secure repository in places where their storage is necessary for the performance of this Agreement, and all other copies will be destroyed in a way that makes it impossible to restore them.
5.4 If possible, the private key of the certificate must be set as non-exportable. The private key of the certificate must always be protected by a strong password and must not be stored in an unencrypted form.
5.5 The Contractor undertakes to immediately inform the Customer of the loss or suspected loss of confidentiality of the private key of the certificate.
6. Handling of Information Assets
6.1 Work with Information Assets is limited only to places that exclude the observation of sensitive information by unauthorized persons. Specifically, it is forbidden to work with Information Assets in public transport, in public places and in places where there is a risk of observation from industrial cameras.
6.2 Upon completion of the work arising from this Agreement, the Contractor shall, without undue delay, return or remove all Information Assets stored in the Contractor's environment, unless the possession of such information is required by the laws of the Czech Republic. This applies to both electronic and paper documentation. The removal of Information Assets must be carried out in a manner that makes it impossible to restore them.
6.3 Without the prior written consent of the Client, the Contractor may not provide access to the Information Assets to any third parties who are not authorized to participate in the performance of this Agreement.
6.4 The Contractor is obliged to ensure adequate security of the computer technology on which the Information Assets are stored, processed or through which they are transmitted. In connection with the Information Assets, the Contractor shall ensure that in the Contractor's environment:
6.4.1 tools are used to encrypt disks, folders and/or files in order to prevent unauthorised access to Information Assets;
6.4.2 tools for the detection and removal of malicious code are used with the setting of regular updates of the database of malicious code signatures with a frequency not exceeding one week and appropriate processes for monitoring, logging and responding to a positive finding of malicious code are set up,
6.4.3 processes for updating security patches of software components are defined, set up, executed and monitored at an interval not exceeding one month from the release of the patches,
6.4.4 the Internet environment is separated by a firewall, which is connected to surveillance, and the Contractor's Persons use only an encrypted VPN connection for remote access, which prevents unauthorized interception and modification of the transmitted communication.
6.5 If the Information Assets are transferred by the Contractor outside the premises of the Authorized Entity, the Contractor is obliged to consistently ensure the physical security of these assets and to keep these Information Assets under constant supervision. The Contractor is obliged to comply with the safety and operating instructions of the manufacturer of the hardware on which the Information Assets are processed.
7. Working in an Authorized Entity Environment
7.1 The Contractor is obliged to become familiar with and act in accordance with the standard for the classification of Information Assets if the Client provides it to him.
7.2 For hardware that is owned and managed by the Customer or hardware that, including its configuration, has been approved in advance by the Customer, the Contractor may not make changes to the configuration of this hardware that have not been approved by the Customer. In particular, the Contractor may not make changes to the security configuration of the hardware. For each hardware installed in this way, the process of applying security patches must be explicitly and formally defined, including the responsibilities arising from the roles within the process.
7.3 Without the prior written consent of the Client, the Contractor may not install or run any software not approved in advance by the Client.
7.4 The Contractor shall not be entitled to carry out any testing of physical or logical security or any type of control mechanisms of the Authorised Entity without the written consent of the Client.
7.5 The contractor must not tamper with the audit records in any way.
7.6 The Contractor's persons are not authorized to work with software, hardware or data content that is not directly related to the performance of this Agreement.
7.7 The Contractor's persons may not carry out any activities harmful to other natural or legal persons, including sending unsolicited emails, sending fraudulent emails, distributing malicious code or participating in attacks aimed at disabling the availability of services.
7.8 The Client logs all steps taken by the Contractor's Persons and keeps a record of them for a period of 3 years.
7.9 Without the written consent of the Client, the Contractor's Persons may not connect their own storage devices to any computer equipment of the Authorized Entity.
7.10 At the provided workplace, the Contractor's Persons are obliged to ensure the following during the period of physical absence:
7.10.1 cleanliness and order so that the workplace can be used safely;
7.10.2 adequate physical security of all Information Assets;
7.10.3 logical locking of access to Information Assets in such a way that unauthorized access to these Information Assets cannot occur.
7.11 Without the prior written consent of the Client, the persons of the Contractor are not entitled to install a device enabling remote listening or to make any audio or video recording.
8. Crisis management
8.1 The Contractor's persons are obliged to prevent, to the greatest extent possible, the occurrence of crisis situations (e.g. fire, explosion, flood, etc.) and situations in which personal injury or damage to the property of the Authorized Person could occur.
8.2 In the event of a crisis situation, the Contractor's Person who is physically present at the place of the event is obliged, without exception and delay, to comply with the regulations and directives in force in the given locality and to obey the instructions for evacuation and protection of persons. This also applies to the case of exercises.
8.3 In the event of crisis management, the Contractor Person is obliged to immediately follow the instructions of the Customer's crisis manager.
9. Reporting of security incidents
9.1 If the Contractor identifies a security incident, he is obliged to report it immediately to the tool https://helpdesk.jtfg.com (telephone: +420.221.710.911).
