Hundreds of enslaved children freed from religious school in Nigeria
According to the BBC, there were nearly five hundred men and boys, Reuters, citing the police commissioner, reported that there were more than three hundred children from the age of five upwards. Some were chained together, others were chained to iron rings in the wall.
The police chief in Kaduna, Ali Janga, told the BBC that the school had been raided on a tip-off, describing it as a "house of horrors" where starving people were held against their will, tortured and sexually abused, unable to leave and with razor wire on the walls - a case of slavery.
